                fnHowtoTempLabelDay: 'Day before',
                fnHowtoTempLabelAuto: 'Auto',
                fnHowtoConnPre: 'FUNCTION\n│\n├──→ REGULAR TASKS — daily/weekly task to assignee automatically\n├──→ TASKS — task.function = name; filtering, analytics, Smart Assign\n├──→ BUSINESS PROCESSES — step = function; Smart Assign from assignees on launch\n├──→ COORDINATIONS — filter tasks "by function participants"\n├──→ BUSINESS STRUCTURE — canvas where functions are connected by arrows\n└──→ FINANCE — expenses and income by function',
                fnGlos0name: 'VFP — Valuable Final Product',
                fnGlos0short: 'One phrase: what exactly this function produces',
                fnGlos0text: 'Answer to the question "what will happen if this department doesn\'t exist?". Not "what they do", but "what appears thanks to them".',
                fnGlos0ex: 'Bad: "Responsible for appointments". Good: "Filled schedule without idle time". System shows VFP to every new employee on day one.',
                fnGlos1name: 'Process',
                fnGlos1short: 'Sequence of actions passing through several departments',
                fnGlos1text: 'Patient called → admin registered → doctor received → cashier invoiced. Each step is a Stage, each Stage is in its own Function.',
                fnGlos1ex: 'Without system: admin registered and forgot to notify doctor. With TALKO: when closed their stage — doctor automatically got a task.',
                fnGlos2name: 'Process stage',
                fnGlos2short: 'One step in a process owned by a specific function',
                fnGlos2text: 'If Process is a relay race, then Stage is the segment run by one specific participant. They receive the task, complete it, pass it on.',
                fnGlos2ex: 'Process "Patient reception": 1) Registration (Admin) → 2) Examination (Medical) → 3) Invoice (Finance) → 4) Payment (Finance).',
                fnGlos3name: 'Function owner',
                fnGlos3short: 'Specific person responsible for function results',
                fnGlos3text: 'Not a position, not a department — a specific name. If a function has no owner — system highlights in red and notifies you. Owner sees all department tasks and gets notifications.',
                fnGlos3ex: 'Maria is the Admin owner. Goes on vacation → assign temporary owner until a specific date. After — rights return automatically.',
                fnGlos4name: 'Metric / KPI',
                fnGlos4short: 'Number showing whether function fulfills its VFP',
                fnGlos4text: 'If VFP is the goal, Metric is the thermometer. Green — normal. Yellow — attention. Red — problem. Each metric tied to a function — immediately clear who is responsible.',
                fnGlos4ex: 'Function "Administration" → metric "Schedule fill rate" → plan 90%, actual 72% → yellow. Who is responsible — visible immediately.',
                fnGlos5name: 'Escalation',
                fnGlos5short: 'Automatic escalation of an issue up the hierarchy',
                fnGlos5text: 'When a task is overdue — system first reminds the responsible. If no reaction in 24 hrs — reminds the manager. Another 24 hrs — writes to you. You receive only what couldn\'t be resolved without you.',
                fnGlos5ex: 'Overdue task: 0 hrs → function owner. +24 hrs → their manager. +48 hrs → you as business owner.',
                fnGlos6name: 'Onboarding',
                fnGlos6short: 'Automatic introduction of new employee to the company',
                fnGlos6text: 'Before: 2-3 hours of explaining who is who. With TALKO: assign person to function — system generates 9-step introduction from function data.',
                fnGlos6ex: 'New doctor from first login: knows who the manager is, where the tasks are, who to interact with, which lessons to take. Owner explained nothing.',
                fnConn0title: 'Function ↔ Tasks',
                fnConn0prob: 'Task without address — who is responsible when a person leaves?',
                fnConn0how: 'Every task is linked to a function. Assignee changed — task function remains. Maria left — tasks stay in Administration, not lost.',
                fnConn0res: '✓ New function owner immediately sees all open department tasks. Nothing needs to be transferred manually.',
                fnConn0loss: '✗ Without link: Maria left → 23 tasks hung → clients got no response → 3-4 lost patients per month.',
                fnConn1title: 'Function ↔ Processes',
                fnConn1prob: 'Someone did their part — and forgot to pass it on',
                fnConn1how: 'Each process stage is linked to its function. Admin closed registration (their stage) → system automatically notified doctor and assigned task. No calls needed.',
                fnConn1res: '✓ Process moves itself. Owner sees where each process is now and which function it got stuck in.',
                fnConn1loss: '✗ Without link: patient registered but doctor doesn\'t know → 30-40 min downtime → 2-3 conflicts per week → reputation losses.',
                fnConn2title: 'Function ↔ People',
                fnConn2prob: 'Person in two departments — where is their priority?',
                fnConn2how: 'Each person has a primary function and secondary ones. Tasks from primary function show first. Plus role: owner (responsible for result) or member (executes tasks).',
                fnConn2res: '✓ Admin-accountant knows: when tasks from both departments — Administration first.',
                fnConn2loss: '✗ Without link: person in two departments always does what\'s convenient → important waits → owner finds out about problem when it\'s too late.',
                fnConn3title: 'Function ↔ Metrics',
                fnConn3prob: 'KPI exists, but unclear who is responsible for it',
                fnConn3how: 'Each metric is linked to a function. Revenue → Sales. Occupancy → Administration. If metric falls below 50% of plan — automatic notification to you.',
                fnConn3res: '✓ Open Administration card — see all department KPIs: plan/actual, color. One point for analysis.',
                fnConn3loss: '✗ Without link: revenue dropped 30% → 2-3 days to understand where the problem is → another week to fix → together ~2 weeks and -$5,000.',
                fnConn4title: 'Function ↔ Finance + Warehouse',
                fnConn4prob: 'How much each department costs — unclear',
                fnConn4how: 'Expenses linked to functions in two ways: direct financial costs (salary, services) and warehouse materials. System sums both flows.',
                fnConn4res: '✓ Function "Medical" per month: salary $2,800 + materials $600 = $3,400. Revenue $8,000. Margin 57%. Visible immediately.',
                fnConn4loss: '✗ Without link: Procurement department spends 40% over budget → $2,000 overspend per quarter → you find out only at the quarterly report.',
                fnConn5title: 'Function ↔ Onboarding',
                fnConn5prob: 'Every new employee — 2-3 hours of explanation',
                fnConn5how: 'When assigning a person to a function — system generates 9-step introduction: manager, VFP, who to interact with, first tasks, lessons. All from function data automatically.',
                fnConn5res: '✓ New admin from first login: knows who the manager is, where to write, what tasks today. You explained nothing.',
                fnConn5loss: '✗ Without link: new doctor first 2 weeks asks colleagues daily → 5-6 hours of lost team time per new employee.',
